          "expected_if_hypothesis_holds": "The value for `rtpengine.loss_ratio` is high (e.g., > 0.1), confirming the primary symptom from the NA report.",
          "falsifying_observation": "The value for `rtpengine.loss_ratio` is within the typical healthy range (0.0, 0.1), which contradicts the evidence the hypothesis is based on.",
          "conflates_with": []
        },
        {
          "tool": "get_dp_quality_gauges",
          "args_hint": "Check UPF in/out symmetry in the output.",
          "expected_if_hypothesis_holds": "UPF packet counters for uplink (N3-in vs N6-out) and downlink (N6-in vs N3-out) are roughly symmetric, indicating the UPF is forwarding traffic correctly and the packet loss occurs at RTPEngine.",
          "falsifying_observation": "UPF packet counters are asymmetric (e.g., N3-in is much higher than N6-out), which points to the UPF as the source of packet loss, falsifying the hypothesis that RTPEngine is the sole source.",
          "conflates_with": []
        }
      ],
      "notes": "The plan focuses on verifying the three key conditions of the hypothesis: RTPEngine is reporting errors, its loss ratio is high, and the adjacent UPF is not the source of the loss. This is anchored to the 'RTP media -- voice call active' step (12) of the 'vonr_call_setup' flow."
    }
  ]
}

